      "name": "GitHub",
      "category": "developer",
      "category_label": "Developer Tools",
      "color": "dracula.purple",
      "kind": "oauth",
      "icon_ref": "lobehub:Github",
      "ws": {
        "login": "github_login",
        "logout": "github_logout",
        "status": "github_status"
      },
      "instructions": "Click 'Login with GitHub' — the gh CLI (auto-installed) opens github.com/login/device in your browser and the one-time code is shown here. The token is stored by gh in your system credential store; OpenCompany never keeps it. After login, 'gh auth setup-git' runs so git remotes authenticate too. Alternative: run 'gh auth login' (or pipe a Personal Access Token to 'gh auth login --with-token') in a terminal on this machine."
    },

