          "key": "cloudflare_api_token",
          "label": "API Token (optional)",
          "type": "password",
          "secret": true,
          "placeholder": "Create at dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens",
          "required": false,
          "help": "Used as CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN on every CLI call and takes precedence over CLI login. The OAuth login carries a fixed scope set with no analytics access beyond DNS — for Web Analytics (RUM), zone analytics, or the GraphQL Analytics API, create a token with 'Account > Account Analytics > Read' (plus 'Zone > Analytics > Read' for zone-scoped queries). The Login button works without it."
        }
      ],
      "instructions": "Two independent auth paths: click 'Login with Cloudflare' — the cf CLI (auto-installed via npm) opens your default browser itself and completes via a localhost callback (browser must run on this machine; the badge flips when the CLI finishes; token stored by cf, never by OpenCompany) — or paste an API token above for full-scope and headless use."
